# GitHub Actions Workflow Standards

## Workflow Structure
- Use descriptive names and clear step descriptions
- Set `fetch-depth: 0` for Git tag access
- Use `persist-credentials: true` for push operations
- Configure proper triggers (push, pull_request, workflow_dispatch)

## Version Bumping Workflows
- [.github/workflows/auto-version.yml](mdc:.github/workflows/auto-version.yml) - Automatic version bumping on master pushes
- [.github/workflows/version-bump.yml](mdc:.github/workflows/version-bump.yml) - Manual version bumping
- Always create Git tags with `v` prefix (e.g., `v1.0.1`)
- Update both `version` file and script content

## Testing Workflows
- [.github/workflows/test-syntax.yml](mdc:.github/workflows/test-syntax.yml) - Syntax and structure testing
- [.github/workflows/test-installation.yml](mdc:.github/workflows/test-installation.yml) - Installation process testing
- [.github/workflows/test-release.yml](mdc:.github/workflows/test-release.yml) - Full release testing

## Common Patterns
- Set executable permissions: `chmod +x yads install.sh modules/*.sh`
- Test line endings: `file script.sh | grep -q "CRLF"`
- Use proper error handling and exit codes
- Generate detailed test reports with emoji indicators

## Path Ignore Patterns
- Ignore documentation files: `README.md`, `MANUAL-UNINSTALL.md`
- Ignore utility scripts: `fix-*.sh`, `test-*.sh`, `manual-uninstall.sh`
- Ignore version files: `version`, `bump-version.sh`
- Ignore Git files: `.gitignore`